# Cursor Rules for Acepe

## Type Checking
- Always run `cargo check` or `cargo clippy` before considering code complete
- Fix all compilation errors before submitting changes
- Address warnings when possible, especially unused variables and dead code

## Code Quality
- Use Rust best practices and follow the existing code style
- Prefer explicit types when the compiler cannot infer them
- Add appropriate error handling and logging

## Testing
- Verify code compiles and runs before marking tasks as complete
- Check for linter errors using `read_lints` tool when editing files

